paragraphs.title: to_spdf
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

from pyspark.sql import Row

solar_angle_list = []

start_dt = datetime.strptime('2017-01-01 00:00', '%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')
end_dt = datetime.strptime('2019-12-31 23:59', '%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')

print('datetime, elevation, hour angle, declination')
while start_dt <= end_dt:
    declination_deg = get_declination(start_dt)
    declination_rad = deg2rad(declination_deg)
    
    hour_angle_deg = get_hour_angle(start_dt)
    hour_angle_rad = deg2rad(hour_angle_deg)

    elevation_rad = get_elevation(declination_rad, lat_rad, hour_angle_rad)
    elevation_deg = rad2deg(elevation_rad)
    
    dt = start_dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')
    solar_angle_list.append(Row(date=dt.split()[0], time=dt.split()[1],
                                solar_zenith=float(rad2deg(0.5*np.pi - elevation_rad)),
                                elevation=float(elevation_deg),
                                hour_angle=float(hour_angle_deg),
                                declination=float(declination_deg)))
    
    start_dt += timedelta(minutes=1)

df = sc.parallelize(solar_angle_list).toDF()
df.show()
df.write.mode('overwrite').parquet('hdfs:///sun/angle_calc.parquet')
